<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN208-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. 
        atiyamāṉ neṭumāṉañciyuḻaicceṉṟa peruñcittiraṉāraik kāṇātu itu koṇṭucelkeṉṟu avaṉparicilkoṭuppak koḷḷātu avar colliyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div xml:id="PN208">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kuṉṟu malaiyum palapi ṉoḻiya</l>
<l>vantaṉeṉ paricil koṇṭaṉeṉ celaṟkeṉa</l>
<l>niṉṟa veṉṉayan taruḷi yītukoṇ</l>
<l>ṭīṅkaṉañ celka tāṉeṉa veṉṉai</l>
<l>yāṅkaṟin taṉaṉō tāṅkaruṅ kāvalaṉ</l>
<l>kāṇā tītta vipporuṭ kiyāṉōr</l>
<l>vāṇikap paricila ṉalleṉ pēṇit</l>
<l>tiṉaiyaṉait tāyiṉu miṉitavar</l>
<l>tuṇaiyaḷa vaṟintu nalkiṉar viṭiṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The [royal] guardian difficult to bear, how did he know (5)</l>
<l>me, to say “having taken this he can go in this manner”, (3d-4)</l>
<l>having graciously longed for me who stood [there] (3a-c)</l>
<l>saying “as hills and mountains many stayed behind, (1)</l>
<l>I have come in order to go as one who has taken a gift.” (2)</l>
<l>For this wealth that was given without seeing I for one (6)</l>
<l>am not a merchant gift seeker. If he had let me go with honour [me] (7+9d)</l>
<l>even if it was as much as a millet [seed], he would have granted</l>
<l>something pleasing, having know to an extent his companion. (8-9c)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
